    "body": "```\r\nIn [19]: df\r\nOut[19]: \r\n   0  1  2\r\n0  1  2  3\r\n1  4  5  6\r\n\r\nIn [20]: arr\r\nOut[20]: \r\narray([[1, 2, 3],\r\n       [4, 5, 6]])\r\n```\r\n\r\ndf[0] selects a *column* of a DataFrame. This is by far a more common operation, whereas ``arr[0]`` is a row-operation.\r\n\r\nyou can use ``df.loc[0]`` to achieve a row operation if you'd like.\r\n\r\npandas has multiple ways of indexing (via positions or labels) and operators for those. the docs are pretty [complete](http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/indexing.html)"
